### Template Method Design Pattern for Sorting Algorithms

#### Abstract Class: `SortAlgorithm`

```java
public abstract class SortAlgorithm {
    public abstract void sort(int[] array);

    public abstract int compare(int i, int j);

    public abstract void swap(int i, int j);
}
```

#### Concrete Subclasses

#### 1. `BubbleSort`

```java
public class BubbleSort extends SortAlgorithm {
    @Override
    public void sort(int[] array) {
        int n = array.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {
                if (compare(j, j + 1) > 0) {
                    swap(j, j + 1);
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

#### 2. `SelectionSort`

```java
public class SelectionSort extends SortAlgorithm {
    @Override
    public void sort(int[] array) {
        int n = array.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int minIndex = i;
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (compare(j, minIndex) < 0) {
                    minIndex = j;
                }
            }
            if (minIndex != i) {
                swap(i, minIndex);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

